   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="uoedh_hl_h.3441_1.jpg"/>
            <!--<pb n="1" facs="uoedh_hl_h.3442_1.jpg"/>-->
            <opener>
               <note rend="pencil" hand="other">
                  <hi rend="underline">Lady Hoare</hi>
               </note>
               <!-- Hardy's? -->

               <address rend="letterhead">
                  <!-- check - embossed -->
                  <addrLine>Stourhead</addrLine>
                  <addrLine>Zeals S.O.</addrLine>
                  <addrLine>Wilts</addrLine>
               </address>
               <!-- Need to add in diagonal embossed letterhead for TELEGRAM STOURTON. STATION, GILLINGHAM LSWR -->
               <dateline>
                  <date when="1914-02-05">
                     <hi rend="underline">Feb' 5<hi rend="SUPERSCRIPT">th</hi>
                        <hi rend="underline">1914</hi></hi>
                  </date>
               </dateline>
               <!-- diagonal text -->

               <salute> Dear M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Hardy</salute>

            </opener>

            <p>Will you <hi rend="underline">permit</hi> me to <hi rend="underline">thank</hi> you
               for using your powerful pen, in the cause of the <hi rend="underline"
               >animals</hi>?</p>
            <p>I have never <pb n="2" facs="uoedh_hl_h.3441_2.jpg"/> for nearly 30 years witnessed
               "Per­forming Animals", nor, as a <hi rend="underline">child</hi>, permitted our son
               to — I thank you, from my heart, for using your great name, &amp; pen, to pillory <pb
                  n="3" facs="uoedh_hl_h.3441_3.jpg"/> these cruel, unnatural, &amp; disgusting
               shows. — </p>
            <closer>
               <salute>
                  <choice><abbr>yrs.</abbr>
                     <expan>yours</expan></choice> very sincerely</salute>
               <signed>Alda Hoare</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb n="4" facs="uoedh_hl_h.3441_4.jpg"/>







         </div>
